Hide Explorer view container title bar (PRO-5559)

The RudderStack sidebar design has no "EXPLORER" header and no
new-file / new-folder / refresh / collapse-all / overflow icons. We
override the `menuActions` getter on `ExplorerViewPaneContainer` (the
same surgical override used by `hide-scm-title-actions.diff`) so the
PaneComposite title toolbar receives no actions, and we add a tiny
CSS rule keyed on the `.explorer-viewlet` body class that the
container adds in `create()` to hide the entire composite title row.

Both changes are reversible by the user via custom CSS or by
rebinding `menuActions`; nothing here uses a settings lock.

